==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Croupous
<hw>Croup"ous</hw> <pr>(kr??p"?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Relating to or resembling croup; especially, attended with the
formation of a deposit or membrane like that found in membranous croup;
<as>as, <ex>croupous</ex> laryngitis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Croupous pneumonia</b></col>, <cd>pneumonia attended with
deposition of fibrinous matter in the air vesicles of the lungs;
ordinary acute pneumonia.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Croupy</ent>⟦br⟧
